 Police have launched investigations after two bodies of unknown men were found near Mankosi forest, in Ngqeleni, at about 15h00 on Thursday. "The bodies were seen by a passerby, who alerted the community in that area," said police spokesperson, Captain Dineo Koena "When police arrived at the scene, it was discovered that both deceased have multiple stab wounds and with their hands tied. "Motive for their killing is not known and no arrest yet." She said that anyone with information may contact D/Lt Col Nodlabi on 079 890 0806 or may contact Crime Stop Line on 0860 010111. 